# SYNC_AXIS.md — your core axis

> The single reference every plan checks against before it's made. The direction that
> shouldn't wobble no matter what the request is. Optional but powerful — if you have a
> north star, put it here and the agent will keep proposals aligned to it.
>
> 모든 기획이 만들어지기 전에 대조하는 단일 레퍼런스. 어떤 요청에도 흔들리면 안 되는
> 방향성. 북극성이 있으면 여기 적으면 에이전트가 제안을 여기 맞춥니다.

## How to use

```
1. before writing any plan/strategy doc, read this file
2. find the relevant axis below
3. check the plan against it — does it pull toward or away from the axis?
4. note the check at the top of the plan doc (a one-line "sync header")
```

## Axes

Format:
```
### [area of life]
- **Axis**: [the principle] — (declared YYYY-MM-DD, source)
```

<!-- Define your core axes below. Examples of areas: your craft, your finances,
     your health, your relationships, your business. Keep each to one clear sentence. -->

### Overall
- **Axis**: {{your single north-star sentence — what everything should serve}}
